For Nihongo novices, choosing between は and が is like a shot in the dark. But don't worry, Japanese sometimes fall into the は-が pitfall too if the sentence is long and complicated. It doesn't make a fatal difference even if you choose the wrong one since the fundamental concepts of は and が are similar, but it does sound weird. Now you ask exactly what differences there are, but it's a tough question to answer briefly since there are many aspects that wa and ga have.

In this article, we are going to see one of these aspects;
